High-Level Description:
This PR implements a standalone task for converting segmentation masks
into object detection targets, inspired by the Retina U-Net framework.
The task extracts bounding boxes and labels from segmentation masks,
enabling joint detection and segmentation training pipelines.

The implementation includes:
- Bounding box extraction from masks
- Support for filtering small objects via min_area
- Batch collation for training pipelines
- Comprehensive unit tests using synthetic data

File Guide:
- pyhealth/tasks/retina_unet_detection.py → main task implementation
- tests/tasks/test_retina_unet_detection.py → unit tests
- examples/retina_unet_task_ablation.py → ablation study
- docs/api/tasks/pyhealth.tasks.retina_unet_detection.rst → documentation

Notes:
This implementation focuses on task-level functionality rather than
full model reproduction, but follows the data processing design used
in Retina U-Net.
